@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@
+# myapp-gstreamer-meson
+
+This example implements a GStreamer GNOME application using puregotk with the [Meson build system](https://mesonbuild.com/), which is the default build system for GTK applications. It shows how to use [GStreamer](https://gstreamer.freedesktop.org/), specifically [`gtk4paintablesink`](https://gstreamer.freedesktop.org/documentation/gtk4/index.html?gi-language=c) in puregotk-based applications. The example is based on the [Python example](https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/gstreamer/gst-plugins-rs/-/blob/main/video/gtk4/examples/gtksink.py?ref_type=heads) and [Rust example](https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/gstreamer/gst-plugins-rs/-/blob/main/video/gtk4/examples/gtksink.rs?ref_type=heads) from [`gst-plugins-rs`](https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/gstreamer/gst-plugins-rs/-/tree/main?ref_type=heads).
+
+First, make sure GStreamer and its plugins are installed on your system.
+
+To then build and install the application using Meson, run:
+
+```shell
+sudo ninja -C _build uninstall || true
+
+meson setup _build --prefix=/usr --wipe && meson compile -C _build && sudo meson install -C _build
+
+myapp-gstreamer-meson
+```
+
+<details>
+    <summary>Expand macOS instructions</summary>
+
+On macOS, `--prefix` depends on your package manager and architecture. Homebrew on macOS uses `/opt/homebrew` for `arm64` and `/usr/local` for `amd64`, MacPorts uses `/opt/local`.
+
+</details>
+
+You can also open the project in [GNOME Builder](https://flathub.org/apps/org.gnome.Builder) and run it by clicking the play button in the header bar.
+
+Alternatively you can use [flatpak-builder](https://docs.flathub.org/docs/for-app-authors/submission#before-submission) directly:
+
+```shell
+$ flatpak run --command=flatpak-builder org.flatpak.Builder --verbose --force-clean --keep-build-dirs --user --ccache --compose-url-policy=full --repo=repo builddir --install page.codeberg.puregotk.MyAppGstreamerMeson.json
+$ flatpak run --command=flatpak-builder-lint org.flatpak.Builder manifest page.codeberg.puregotk.MyAppGstreamerMeson.json
+$ flatpak run --command=flatpak-builder-lint org.flatpak.Builder repo repo
+$ flatpak run page.codeberg.puregotk.MyAppGstreamerMeson
+```
+
+We're disabling the sandbox here because otherwise we can't access the Go cache on the system.
+
+![Screenshot of myapp-gstreamer-meson showing the main application window](../../docs/screenshot-myapp-gstreamer-meson.png)
